@database "Extention.guide"
@width 80
@node main "Extention List Contents"

       @{b} Amiga Guide Extention Lister

       By Robbie Wegner. V1.7@{ub}

    Click here to @{"Search" system "run s:ExtListersearch Sample4.Guide.0 "} for string.

 List of @{" Song Moduals " link " .mod 10000"} Archives:AMINET10/Aminet/mods/funk/

 List of @{" Song Moduals " link " .mod 10001"} Archives:AMINET10/Aminet/mods/piano/

 List of @{" Song Moduals " link " .mod 10002"} Archives:AMINET10/Aminet/mods/rock/

 List of @{" Song Moduals " link " .mod 10003"} Archives:AMINET10/Aminet/mods/slow/

INFO-

  This is a small sample guide generated by the ExtLister script to look at
 songmoduals off the Aminet 10 CD using ARCHANDLER and the modual player HIP-po.
 I have only listed .mod files from a few sub-directories in the "Mods"
 directory.
 (ARCHANDLER lets you read LHA files like normal directories).

  If you have these set up, you should be able to click on a button and load
 and play the moduals automatically. If you like a Song, use the copy button
 to add it to your Modual collection!

  Song moduals with out extentions would be a problem to find, but using the
 "All Extentions" function, you  could get most of the songs listed in the
 Mods directory. (Plus all the other junk in there as well unfortunately) But
 would be an easier way of checking out which are the better moduals.
   Mods with spaces in their file names will be un-usable! See PROBLEMS in the Doc
 Guide about AmigaGuides limitations.

  The "Extra Function Button" is set to the ExtCopy script that will copy the
 Modual to a directory of your choice. (It will ask for a destination on the
 first usage, and then use that destination from then on for the other copy
 buttons. (See "Instalation" in the guide for more about the ExtCopy script). 

  This is a Same Extentions across all selections Guide, with the file name
 and path in the lists switched off.

 If you have the Aminet10 CD, ARCHANDLER and HIP player, you can try out the guide.
 The search and Copy functions will not work until the s directory scripts are
 installed and AskEnv is installed in the C: directory.

@endnode
